    <body>
      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Create an accelerated depreciation profile and assign it to book (Japan)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>For Japan, accelerated depreciation requires configuration of a depreciation profile, just like other depreciation methods.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create an accelerated depreciation profile and assign it to book (Japan)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For Japan, accelerated depreciation requires configuration of a depreciation profile, just like other depreciation methods.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use this procedure to learn how to create a depreciation profile for accelerated depreciation and assign it to a book.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In order to complete this procedure, the Fixed Asset configuration key must be selected.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This procedure was created using the demo data company JPMF.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create a depreciation profile</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Fixed assets &gt; Setup &gt; Depreciation profiles.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click New.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Depreciation profile field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Note the value in the Depreciation profile field to reference later</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Name field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Method field, select 'Accelerated'.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Assign the depreciation profile to a book</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Fixed assets &gt; Setup &gt; Books.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select the book to assign the accelerated depreciation profile to.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Edit.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use the value noted previously in the Accelerated depreciation profile field</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
